To refactor a lightweight TypeScript helper for logistics after handling flaky retries, consider the following minimal safe fix:

```typescript
async function retryWithBackoff<T>(fn: () => Promise<T>, maxRetries = 3): Promise<T> {
    let attempts = 0;
    while (attempts < maxRetries) {
        try {
            return await fn();
        } catch (error) {
            attempts++;
            if (attempts === maxRetries) throw error;
            const delay = Math.pow(2, attempts) * 100; // Exponential backoff
            await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, delay));
        }
    }
}
```

This function retries the provided asynchronous function up to `maxRetries` times with exponential backoff. It catches errors and waits before retrying until it either succeeds or reaches the maximum number of attempts.

